Global Non-ferrous Metal Recycling Market Insights
Non-ferrous Metal Recycling Market size was valued at USD 30 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 45 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Non-ferrous Metal Recycling Market Overview
The global non-ferrous metal recycling market was valued at approximately USD 60 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of around 6% over the forecast period from 2025 to 2030. This market encompasses the recycling of metals like aluminum, copper, lead, and zinc, which are non-ferrous in nature and do not contain significant amounts of iron. These metals are highly valuable due to their durability, lightweight properties, and wide range of industrial applications. Growing environmental concerns and increasing demand for sustainable practices are major factors contributing to the market's expansion. The Asia-Pacific region leads in market share, driven by rapid industrialization and urbanization in countries like China and India. Moreover, technological advancements and improved recycling processes are expected to further boost the growth of the market.

