7. Is the non-ferrous metal recycling market growing?
Yes, the market is expected to grow at a CAGR of around 6% from 2025 to 2030.

8. What metals are considered non-ferrous?
Common non-ferrous metals include aluminum, copper, lead, zinc, and nickel.

9. How does technological advancement affect the market?
Technological advancements improve recycling efficiency and cost-effectiveness, boosting market growth.

10. Why is recycling non-ferrous metals important?
Recycling non-ferrous metals helps conserve natural resources, reduce waste, and lower carbon emissions associated with metal production.

